Answer What‚Äôs the difference between a ‚Äúdeck-mounted‚Äù skylight and a ‚Äúcurb-mounted‚Äù skylight? On top of a framed aperture in the roof, curb-mounted skylights are installed. Deck-mounted skylights attach to the roof sheathing directly, eliminating the need for a framed curb.   As a result, what does a deck mounted skylight imply? Does coolant have to be the same color?

07 Sep 2024, 00:00

What colors does coolant come in? Variations of coolant/antifreeze can come in; pink, red, orange, blue, green, and yellow. This can make it confusing when trying to decide which coolant you need in your vehicle. The different colors can mean different properties of the liquid. Is it OK to mix different color coolants? It's never a good idea to mix two different colors or types of antifreeze. Mixing two formulas won't cause any dangerous reactions or explosions, but it could turn your coolant into a sludgy chemical mixture that won't be able to flow properly through your cooling system.

Why did the NHL add the trapezoid?

27 Aug 2024, 00:00

To combat low-scoring and slow hockey, the NHL created the trapezoid in 2004. Legendary New Jersey Devils goaltender Martin Brodeur is often credited with forcing the NHL to implement the trapezoid. Why did the NHL make the trapezoid rule? The trapezoid rule, also known as Rule 1.8 in the NHL rulebook, was introduced after the 2004-05 lockout. Brodeur, a phenomenal puck-handling goaltender, was one of the chief reasons for the introduction of the rule as the NHL tried to cut down on goalies leaving their crease to stop dump-ins in the corners.

What does N mean on a car?

16 Aug 2024, 00:00

The ‚ÄúN‚Äù is an indicator that your automatic transmission is in NEUTRAL or a free spinning mode. This setting releases the gear(s) (forward and reverse) and allows the tires to spin freely. Most people do not use the N setting unless their car engine will not start and they need to push it or have the vehicle towed. Can you drive in neutral? Unlike the drive and reverse gears, neutral isn't intended for use when driving the car.
